{
  "doc_id": "55475",
  "text": "One caveat of this study is that axonal regeneration is influenced by factors that can be produced by the peripheral system, such as IL-1 and TGF-beta, as these cytokines affect glial scar formation [CITATION_1] . Rac1 is also an important mediator of immunity, and inhibition of Rac1 in peripheral blood mononuclear cells from human blood was shown to reduce IL-1 beta release [CITATION_2] . Although manipulation of Rac1 provides considerable evidence for a combined effect of both central and peripheral responses, brain injection of lentivirus may not allow us to observe peripheral effects. We will closely monitor changes in cytokines using peripheral blood samples. This approach will also help to evaluate the possible role of Rac1 in post-stroke inflammation, as Rac1 is known to participate in the immune response [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
